# 🧠 flask-memory-app

A simple Flask web app that stores phrases and tones in memory — locally and temporarily — through both form input and JSON POST requests.

---

## 🌐 Live Preview

When running locally, open [http://127.0.0.1:5000](http://127.0.0.1:5000)

---

## 📋 Features

- Submit a **phrase** and **tone** via HTML form
- Send data via `POST` using JSON (`Content-Type: application/json`)
- View all memory entries at `/memory`
- Rate-limited to prevent spam (`100 requests/min` per IP)

